WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:53.762 --> 00:55.263
[Tae-seo sobbing]

00:55.346 --> 00:57.056
[melancholy music playing]

01:00.518 --> 01:02.520
[door opens, closes]

01:21.039 --> 01:22.540
[Chang-sik] Tae-seo, is that you?

01:27.170 --> 01:28.838
Yes, it's me.

01:31.633 --> 01:34.344
If you're done crying, let's go home.

01:35.136 --> 01:38.223
Get some rest
so you can go back to Seoul and work.

01:39.516 --> 01:40.600
Come on!

01:41.726 --> 01:42.769
Okay!

01:56.533 --> 01:57.951
[shudders]

02:07.043 --> 02:14.008
STILL SHINING

02:15.176 --> 02:16.845
[music fades]

02:16.928 --> 02:23.893
MART

02:24.519 --> 02:26.229
[grunts, clears throat]

02:28.106 --> 02:30.859
[vocalizing]

02:30.942 --> 02:32.235
[cackles]

02:37.782 --> 02:41.161
[Hui-seo] You can just say
whatever comes to mind.

02:41.244 --> 02:45.081
Like when you have some <i>makgeolli</i>
and go out on a stroll together.

02:45.165 --> 02:46.082
Okay.

02:47.250 --> 02:50.420
I know what your grandma likes.

02:51.337 --> 02:53.172
[Gyeong-chun clearing throat]

02:58.803 --> 03:04.601
♪ <i>The pale pink skirt</i> ♪

03:06.311 --> 03:11.107
♪ <i>Flutters in the spring breeze</i> ♪

03:12.650 --> 03:18.907
♪ <i>Biting the ribbon of my blouse</i>
<i>Again today</i> ♪

03:18.990 --> 03:20.658
[heartwarming music playing]

03:20.742 --> 03:26.915
♪ <i>Along the village shrine road</i>
<i>Where butterflies flit to and fro</i> ♪

03:27.999 --> 03:31.502
♪ <i>When flowers bloomed</i> ♪

03:31.586 --> 03:35.298
♪ <i>We laughed together</i> ♪

03:35.381 --> 03:38.593
♪ <i>When flowers fell</i> ♪

03:38.676 --> 03:41.596
[voice breaking] ♪ <i>We cried together</i> ♪

03:42.805 --> 03:49.354
♪ <i>Yet with that earnest promise</i> ♪

03:49.437 --> 03:52.732
♪ <i>The spring days</i> ♪

03:53.816 --> 03:56.611
♪ <i>Are gone</i> ♪

04:03.201 --> 04:04.202
[music fades]

04:15.588 --> 04:17.590
[gentle music playing]

04:39.696 --> 04:40.655
[woman] Oh my gosh!

04:40.738 --> 04:43.157
You put the photos on the outside
so it's easy to tell.

04:43.241 --> 04:44.909
Great job.

04:44.993 --> 04:46.744
But I like that one.

04:48.121 --> 04:49.289
OIDO STATION, SNOW, WINTER

04:49.372 --> 04:50.206
[Tae-seo] Me too.

04:50.290 --> 04:52.000
[woman] Wow, you did a really good job.

04:52.875 --> 04:53.918
Great job on these!

04:57.797 --> 04:58.798
Do you want it?

05:12.395 --> 05:13.896
[music fades]

05:14.939 --> 05:16.524
[doorbell rings]

05:30.038 --> 05:31.873
-[keypad dings]
-[door opens]

05:31.956 --> 05:32.957
[Tae-seo] Mmm.

05:37.962 --> 05:39.047
You can wear those.

05:40.882 --> 05:42.425
Check what I've done so far.

05:47.472 --> 05:48.431
[A-sol] Mmm.

05:52.351 --> 05:55.104
It really does feel like
it's being embraced.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.440
It feels warm.

05:58.691 --> 06:00.318
Mmm? That one's mine.

06:03.821 --> 06:05.239
I've oiled it.

06:05.823 --> 06:06.657
It needs to dry.

06:07.575 --> 06:08.826
So you're all done.

06:08.910 --> 06:11.788
You said after waiting a day
for oiling, that's it.

06:11.871 --> 06:14.999
The third and final moment of waiting.

06:17.668 --> 06:19.670
I'll wrap this up for you.

06:19.754 --> 06:20.838
I'll help you.

06:21.631 --> 06:23.049
I can do it by myself.

06:25.968 --> 06:27.095
[exhales heavily]

06:28.304 --> 06:29.722
KTC RAILWAY LAWS AND REGULATIONS

06:34.769 --> 06:37.605
You're juggling five balls at once.

06:37.688 --> 06:39.524
Of course you'd be overwhelmed.

06:40.441 --> 06:41.818
Why five?

06:41.901 --> 06:44.821
Your job, your side gig,
preparing to change jobs,

06:44.904 --> 06:47.532
family issues, and relationship issues.

06:48.324 --> 06:50.827
Isn't that how everyone lives?

06:50.910 --> 06:52.870
You sure you're doing well?

06:54.205 --> 06:55.915
What is it that you want to know?

06:57.250 --> 06:59.627
I heard things aren't going well
with your girlfriend.

07:00.711 --> 07:03.840
Hyeong-seok said
after he broke up, so did you.

07:06.425 --> 07:07.385
Did you know?

07:08.261 --> 07:09.595
The number of people you've dated

07:09.679 --> 07:12.056
doesn't always match
the number you've broken up with.

07:12.723 --> 07:15.393
The number of breakups is usually lower.

07:15.476 --> 07:18.146
Breaking up with someone
is a memorable experience.

07:19.147 --> 07:22.358
Even with my friends,
they've dated several people,

07:22.442 --> 07:25.278
but they only ever talk about one breakup.

07:25.361 --> 07:29.323
I guess you have to remember the breakup
for it to count as a real relationship.

07:31.659 --> 07:33.453
[cellphone vibrating]

07:33.536 --> 07:35.329
HUI-SEO

07:35.413 --> 07:36.372
[Tae-seo] Hold on.

07:40.126 --> 07:42.211
-Hey, Hui-seo.
-[Hui-seo] <i>Hey, Tae-seo.</i>

07:42.295 --> 07:44.255
<i>Can you come to the hospital today?</i>

07:44.338 --> 07:45.882
Well, I am off today. What's up?

07:45.965 --> 07:49.510
This morning,
the corner of Grandma's mouth twitched.

07:50.261 --> 07:51.929
You know,

07:52.013 --> 07:54.682
it's like how Grandma always smirks
when she sees me.

07:54.765 --> 07:56.100
<i>Anyway, it moved.</i>

07:56.184 --> 07:57.685
What did the doctor say?

07:57.768 --> 08:01.355
<i>No, it's not what the doctor said.</i>
<i>I saw it myself.</i>

08:02.899 --> 08:04.025
[sentimental music playing]

08:04.108 --> 08:06.527
So what do you expect me to come and do?

08:06.611 --> 08:08.654
<i>She might wake up, so…</i>

08:10.031 --> 08:11.199
Fine.

08:12.200 --> 08:14.285
I'll tell Grandpa to go home,

08:14.911 --> 08:16.162
<i>and I'll stay here myself.</i>

08:16.871 --> 08:18.289
Go home. I'll be there.

08:18.372 --> 08:19.332
<i>I'm getting a call.</i>

08:20.791 --> 08:21.709
It's A-sol.

08:23.836 --> 08:25.129
Hi, Hui-seo.

08:26.547 --> 08:27.840
If I come down today,

08:27.924 --> 08:30.468
can I get
that red carpet treatment you mentioned?

08:31.469 --> 08:34.805
I'm seeing Tae-seo today to get my frame,
so I might suggest we go together.

08:36.182 --> 08:38.434
I've had so much work lately.

08:38.518 --> 08:40.436
You know I like
to blow off steam by driving.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.064
[chuckling] Yeah, exactly.

08:44.106 --> 08:46.567
You know a place like that?
That sounds delicious.

08:47.944 --> 08:49.612
Okay. Bye.

08:51.322 --> 08:53.366
I'll drive, so you can get
some sleep on the way.

08:53.449 --> 08:54.784
I can go by myself.

08:54.867 --> 08:56.786
Don't you have work tomorrow?

08:56.869 --> 08:59.413
-I do.
-Then you have to come back anyway.

08:59.497 --> 09:03.125
If we leave now, eat,
see your grandma, and come back,

09:03.209 --> 09:04.877
it'll be perfect timing.

09:16.138 --> 09:18.933
Always with bloodshot eyes
from lack of sleep,

09:19.016 --> 09:21.227
the study center's Seat One guy

09:21.310 --> 09:23.604
doesn't seem like
the type to easily fall for someone.

09:24.188 --> 09:26.357
And even when he does like someone,

09:26.440 --> 09:28.859
he doesn't seem like
the type to break up easily.

09:30.820 --> 09:32.613
So how did he break up
the very first time?

09:34.782 --> 09:36.784
This is based on the people around me,

09:36.867 --> 09:41.414
but how your first breakup happens
has a bigger impact than your first love.

09:43.791 --> 09:45.418
I'm curious.

09:45.501 --> 09:48.879
When and how did Seat One guy break up?

09:49.463 --> 09:50.840
How did he feel?

09:51.674 --> 09:53.134
Not that he'd tell me.

09:53.217 --> 09:54.176
Stunned.

09:55.553 --> 09:56.387
Hmm? What was that?

09:57.471 --> 09:58.306
Mmm.

10:01.017 --> 10:02.393
Then what about the second time?

10:06.772 --> 10:08.733
No second time? Just the one?

10:10.276 --> 10:11.360
The same person.

10:11.944 --> 10:12.778
Ah.

10:15.948 --> 10:18.534
Wake me up at the first rest stop.

10:18.618 --> 10:19.619
Okay.

10:21.329 --> 10:23.331
[monitor beeping]

10:40.681 --> 10:42.600
[panting]

10:48.939 --> 10:50.232
[splashing]

10:57.782 --> 11:00.868
[cellphone vibrating]

11:05.331 --> 11:06.374
Hello?

11:07.249 --> 11:10.127
Yes, I'm Yeon Tae-seo's brother,
Yeon Hui-seo.

11:12.421 --> 11:14.715
[splutters] Okay, I'll come now.

11:14.799 --> 11:16.300
I'll be right there.

11:16.384 --> 11:17.218
Okay, bye.

11:17.301 --> 11:19.303
[pleasant music playing]

11:27.186 --> 11:28.062
Hey, guys!

11:28.979 --> 11:30.189
Thank you!

11:36.570 --> 11:39.907
[line ringing]

11:45.955 --> 11:47.915
Damn it, why isn't he picking up?

11:47.998 --> 11:49.834
[grunting]

11:49.917 --> 11:51.585
[cellphone ringing]

11:52.586 --> 11:54.755
[Hui-seo] <i>A-sol, is my brother with you?</i>

11:54.839 --> 11:56.549
-Yes.
<i>-My brother.</i>

11:56.632 --> 11:58.342
<i>Hey, Tae-seo. Wake up.</i>

12:01.345 --> 12:03.264
Yeah, Hui-seo. I'm on my way.

12:03.848 --> 12:04.849
Tae-seo.

12:04.932 --> 12:06.559
They said Grandma woke up.

12:06.642 --> 12:08.602
I just got a call from the hospital.

12:08.686 --> 12:09.603
I told you, didn't I?

12:10.438 --> 12:11.647
<i>Hurry up and get there.</i>

12:11.730 --> 12:13.941
-Okay, I'll go straight there.
<i>-Okay.</i>

12:15.568 --> 12:17.403
Grandpa. [grunts]

12:18.070 --> 12:19.947
Grandpa, get up.

12:20.948 --> 12:22.324
Get up! They said Grandma's awake.

12:23.200 --> 12:24.243
What?

12:25.244 --> 12:27.413
-[Hui-seo whispers] Hurry and get up.
-Okay.

12:31.459 --> 12:32.585
[grunts]

12:32.668 --> 12:33.669
[music fades]

12:34.670 --> 12:36.505
Gosh! Oh, goodness.

12:36.589 --> 12:37.715
Oh, oh.

12:38.215 --> 12:40.509
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

12:40.593 --> 12:43.220
Grandpa, will you be able to drive?

12:44.305 --> 12:45.514
I have to.

12:46.182 --> 12:48.934
I just woke up,
so my legs have no strength.

12:49.977 --> 12:51.270
-What about your hands?
-What?

12:51.353 --> 12:53.063
Can you grip like this?

12:53.147 --> 12:54.273
My hands?

12:57.109 --> 12:59.069
[grunting] Like this?

13:00.905 --> 13:02.907
[uplifting music playing]

13:05.659 --> 13:07.495
Your helmet's on okay, right?

13:08.496 --> 13:10.539
-Hold tight!
-Okay.

13:10.623 --> 13:11.999
You can't let go.

13:13.000 --> 13:14.543
But…

13:14.627 --> 13:17.546
you've never ridden
past the post office before.

13:17.630 --> 13:19.256
Will you be okay?

13:19.882 --> 13:21.091
I have to be.

13:21.675 --> 13:23.260
Grandma found the strength too.

13:38.150 --> 13:39.944
-[doctor 1] Just a second.
-Yes, Doctor.

13:40.027 --> 13:42.279
Why do things seem so serious?

13:42.363 --> 13:43.364
[music fades]

13:43.447 --> 13:45.032
Before passing away,

13:45.908 --> 13:47.910
she might've regained
some momentary consciousness.

13:47.993 --> 13:50.120
[shudders] Like terminal lucidity.

13:52.581 --> 13:54.750
-[doctor 2] Her breathing is stabilizing…
-Her hand.

13:55.960 --> 13:56.794
What?

13:58.587 --> 14:01.632
Her index finger twitched.

14:02.591 --> 14:03.425
It's twitching.

14:04.260 --> 14:06.262
[heartwarming music playing]

14:14.687 --> 14:16.105
[doctor 1] Everything looks normal.

14:18.107 --> 14:19.441
[A-sol exclaims softly]

14:20.818 --> 14:23.279
She really is awake.

14:35.791 --> 14:37.793
Please explain to the patient's family.

14:37.877 --> 14:40.087
-[nurse] Her condition is stable…
-[sighs]

14:40.170 --> 14:42.506
…so please go put on
your isolation gowns first.

14:44.758 --> 14:49.430
[A-sol] <i>Dad, have you been</i>
<i>to the hospital? How are you feeling?</i>

14:53.392 --> 14:54.560
So…

14:55.811 --> 14:56.645
I'll…

14:58.314 --> 15:01.358
find a way to manage by myself for a year.

15:08.115 --> 15:10.117
You said you'd come back
to work next year.

15:13.662 --> 15:15.497
Make sure you keep your promise.

15:17.333 --> 15:18.542
Okay, bye.

15:26.717 --> 15:27.718
[music fades]

15:27.801 --> 15:32.681
[Chang-sik] Yeah.
She really pulled through. [chuckles]

15:32.765 --> 15:35.225
Apparently, it was no easy thing. [laughs]

15:35.309 --> 15:37.645
Anyway, thanks. Bye.

15:40.397 --> 15:41.357
[Chang-sik sighs]

15:44.193 --> 15:46.570
I've called the village chief,
so everyone will know.

15:47.988 --> 15:49.573
Call everyone on your way home.

15:50.407 --> 15:55.496
Everyone's well wishes
helped make this happen.

15:56.246 --> 15:57.289
Okay.

15:57.373 --> 15:59.041
[Hui-seo] Right?

15:59.124 --> 16:01.251
I told you she would wake up soon.

16:01.835 --> 16:04.755
[chuckles softly]
No, you don't have to come, Hyang-gi.

16:05.506 --> 16:08.759
You can visit
when she moves to a regular room.

16:09.760 --> 16:11.595
No, I should be thanking you.

16:22.231 --> 16:24.233
[pensive music playing]

16:26.110 --> 16:28.529
[shudders, exhales heavily]

16:32.074 --> 16:33.867
[exhales heavily]

16:36.120 --> 16:37.955
[exhales shakily]

16:48.007 --> 16:49.049
I'll drive.

16:49.133 --> 16:50.509
Can you manage?

16:50.592 --> 16:51.468
Yeah.

16:53.554 --> 16:54.722
Hey…

16:57.016 --> 16:58.642
You insisted that we come.

17:02.771 --> 17:03.689
Thank you.

17:23.542 --> 17:24.543
[music fades]

17:53.530 --> 17:54.531
[sighs]

17:56.075 --> 17:57.367
Grandma…

17:58.994 --> 18:00.996
[emotional music playing]

18:02.623 --> 18:03.999
…woke up.

18:25.145 --> 18:27.606
[Gyeong-chun] <i>I went and sang to her,</i>

18:27.689 --> 18:30.109
<i>and the next day,</i>
<i>she woke up just like that.</i>

18:30.192 --> 18:31.318
[sighs in relief]

18:32.569 --> 18:33.612
[music fades]

18:33.695 --> 18:34.696
[shudders]

18:34.780 --> 18:37.032
[voice breaking]
Well, you're really good at singing.

18:38.075 --> 18:39.576
Aren't you coming back here?

18:39.660 --> 18:42.162
Want me to submit another request
to tear down your house?

18:42.246 --> 18:44.498
[Eun-a] <i>No, don't.</i>

18:44.581 --> 18:46.333
Gosh.

18:46.416 --> 18:49.545
If you came back
and Hui-seo's family came back,

18:49.628 --> 18:50.921
wouldn't that be so nice?

18:53.173 --> 18:57.010
<i>Make sure you eat properly.</i>
<i>Don't skip your meals.</i>

18:57.094 --> 18:58.220
Okay.

18:59.138 --> 19:00.973
Make sure you eat too, Granny.

19:02.432 --> 19:03.600
Bye.

19:12.151 --> 19:13.402
[shudders]

19:14.444 --> 19:16.029
That's great.

19:17.614 --> 19:20.909
He can go back home

19:22.744 --> 19:24.705
and back to the way he was living.

19:25.664 --> 19:26.999
[soft music playing]

19:27.082 --> 19:30.711
[Eun-a] <i>After work,</i>
<i>he'll run across Dongjak Bridge,</i>

19:30.794 --> 19:35.048
<i>ride a public rental bicycle up the hill,</i>
<i>and continue his woodwork.</i>

19:35.132 --> 19:36.383
Hello!

19:37.176 --> 19:39.219
[Eun-a] <i>He'll see his friend</i>
<i>every now and then.</i>

19:40.012 --> 19:40.846
Thanks.

19:40.929 --> 19:42.639
Oh, you're here.

19:42.723 --> 19:45.058
Gosh, I'm really craving
some rolled omelets.

19:45.142 --> 19:46.894
[man] Okay, I'll make you some.

19:47.769 --> 19:49.146
[Eun-a] <i>The simple,</i>

19:50.564 --> 19:51.607
peaceful…

19:53.275 --> 19:54.568
[chuckles softly]

19:54.651 --> 19:56.778
…and precious routine of Yeon Tae-seo.

20:01.909 --> 20:02.743
[A-sol] <i>Tae-seo.</i>

20:02.826 --> 20:03.702
[music fades]

20:03.785 --> 20:04.620
Hey.

20:05.704 --> 20:07.164
Did you already get off work?

20:07.247 --> 20:10.709
No, I went to eat dinner
and came right back.

20:11.376 --> 20:14.463
-Did you bring my frame?
-Yeah, since I was coming anyway.

20:14.546 --> 20:16.590
I probably won't see you much from now on.

20:16.673 --> 20:19.593
Where's your car? I'll load it in for you.

20:19.676 --> 20:21.762
Oh… It's in the parking lot over there.

20:26.141 --> 20:27.851
It must've been hard getting here by taxi.

20:27.935 --> 20:29.228
I took the bus.

20:30.103 --> 20:31.855
You should've called me.

20:31.939 --> 20:34.107
It would've been easier
if I picked it up myself.

20:34.191 --> 20:36.151
No, it's fine.

20:36.235 --> 20:38.445
-Where should I put these?
-I'll take them.

20:38.528 --> 20:39.947
Okay.

20:43.909 --> 20:45.285
How long will it take?

20:45.369 --> 20:46.620
[Tae-seo] It won't take long.

20:49.039 --> 20:51.959
So you'll finish everything today
and never see me again?

20:52.042 --> 20:55.379
I'm strapped for time since I'm trying
to change jobs while working.

20:57.005 --> 20:59.716
[sighs] I don't get it.

21:00.676 --> 21:04.054
You were preparing to change jobs
before your grandma woke up.

21:04.137 --> 21:05.973
And she's awake now.

21:06.056 --> 21:08.475
Everything's still the same, so why?

21:08.558 --> 21:10.060
I was going to do it anyway.

21:10.894 --> 21:13.146
It's better to do it now
when I've made up my mind.

21:14.147 --> 21:15.315
[sighs]

21:17.484 --> 21:19.820
[A-sol] Are you done now? That was quick.

21:20.529 --> 21:21.738
[Tae-seo] By the way,

21:21.822 --> 21:24.533
it'll dry faster with some air,
so leave the window open later.

21:25.450 --> 21:26.451
Okay.

21:26.952 --> 21:28.203
Uh… [sighs]

21:30.497 --> 21:32.582
I don't know if I'll get to see you, but…

21:34.376 --> 21:35.210
Thanks.

21:35.294 --> 21:37.004
For what?

21:39.464 --> 21:42.926
[chuckles] Not now.
Tell me when we say goodbye.

21:43.010 --> 21:47.681
Let's grab a drink with Hyeong-seok
after I finish preparing my job switch.

21:47.764 --> 21:49.891
No, not that.

21:50.892 --> 21:52.394
Let's do this instead.

21:53.353 --> 21:56.064
If you want to thank me, do me one favor.

21:56.982 --> 21:57.816
What is it?

21:57.899 --> 21:59.359
I already said it.

22:00.527 --> 22:01.820
I want us to break up.

22:01.903 --> 22:05.907
Um, this isn't some roundabout way
of saying we should date.

22:06.867 --> 22:07.701
[sighs]

22:08.952 --> 22:11.830
I've never been
in a proper relationship before,

22:11.913 --> 22:14.041
so I've never really
broken up with anyone either.

22:14.666 --> 22:18.503
I don't want my first-ever parting
to be with my family.

22:20.589 --> 22:24.343
I want my first goodbye to be a warm one.

22:24.426 --> 22:25.719
[sentimental music playing]

22:25.802 --> 22:27.471
There's no such thing as a warm breakup.

22:27.554 --> 22:29.306
[A-sol] That's what I want.

22:32.309 --> 22:34.644
I want my first goodbye to be just that.

22:35.228 --> 22:36.480
That's why I'm asking you.

22:38.815 --> 22:39.900
[sighing] We weren't…

22:39.983 --> 22:41.693
We weren't even dating though.

22:41.777 --> 22:43.820
Uh… Think of it like this.

22:43.904 --> 22:47.115
You're here just to oil the desk,

22:47.199 --> 22:48.742
but I'm dating you right now.

22:48.825 --> 22:52.204
I'm dating and breaking up with you
all on my own.

22:52.287 --> 22:54.831
This actually makes a lot of sense.

22:54.915 --> 22:56.208
I had feelings for you…

22:56.291 --> 22:58.668
Well, it was a mix of feelings,
like sympathy and so on.

22:58.752 --> 23:00.253
But anyway, after ten years,

23:00.337 --> 23:03.507
I went to commission a frame
and just happened to reunite with you.

23:03.590 --> 23:05.092
That was a big part of it.

23:05.175 --> 23:10.180
So after getting all excited on my own
and wondering if it was a thing or not,

23:10.263 --> 23:11.348
I'm breaking up with you.

23:13.058 --> 23:16.686
[sighs] Do you seriously think
this makes any sense?

23:18.605 --> 23:21.066
Don't overthink it. Just…

23:21.817 --> 23:23.652
think of it as doing me a favor.

23:26.571 --> 23:27.489
[sighs]

23:29.282 --> 23:30.450
So,

23:31.493 --> 23:32.911
how do you want to break up then?

23:32.994 --> 23:35.455
You only need to do one thing.

23:36.206 --> 23:37.582
On the day we break up,

23:38.708 --> 23:42.003
we'll hold hands, face each other,

23:42.087 --> 23:47.467
and say what we had been thankful for.

23:48.468 --> 23:49.469
With warmth.

23:50.887 --> 23:53.348
That's the first breakup
I've always wanted.

23:53.431 --> 23:54.933
And after we break up?

23:57.352 --> 23:58.520
After we break up,

23:59.271 --> 24:00.730
we won't see each other ever again.

24:01.356 --> 24:03.358
That's why we're saying goodbye.

24:04.109 --> 24:07.320
You were going to stop
seeing me after today anyway.

24:09.823 --> 24:15.287
If my first goodbye is a warm one,
any goodbye that comes after that,

24:16.955 --> 24:18.623
even if it's with family,

24:20.333 --> 24:21.877
won't feel so scary anymore.

24:24.087 --> 24:26.173
And if it's with the guy from Seat One,

24:27.716 --> 24:28.925
it'll be special.

24:30.177 --> 24:31.469
And I'd be grateful.

24:34.848 --> 24:35.849
[Tae-seo sniffles]

24:40.312 --> 24:42.606
-You're not going?
-You haven't given me an answer.

24:44.441 --> 24:45.692
I'll do it.

24:48.236 --> 24:49.404
It's not even that difficult.

24:54.534 --> 24:55.952
[sighs]

25:00.790 --> 25:02.000
[cellphone vibrates]

25:05.879 --> 25:06.880
[music fades]

25:06.963 --> 25:09.591
[A-sol] <i>How about</i>
<i>after you finish your test,</i>

25:09.674 --> 25:12.302
<i>around the second week of December?</i>

25:12.385 --> 25:14.221
<i>But not December 8th.</i>

25:14.304 --> 25:16.932
<i>I don't think breaking up</i>
<i>on a Monday is a good idea.</i>

25:17.015 --> 25:18.808
<i>I'll pick the place.</i>

25:22.103 --> 25:24.940
[Tae-seo] <i>The place we broke up…</i>

25:25.023 --> 25:27.025
[sentimental music playing]

25:35.575 --> 25:36.534
<i>Where did you…</i>

25:38.620 --> 25:40.372
<i>break up with me?</i>

25:54.386 --> 25:58.807
WONMA EATERY

25:58.890 --> 26:00.684
-[Hyeong-seok] Hello.
-[man] Hey.

26:02.519 --> 26:03.728
He's dying over there.

26:09.651 --> 26:10.652
[music fades]

26:10.735 --> 26:12.195
Everyone goes through breakups.

26:13.863 --> 26:15.657
Let's finish this bottle and go home.

26:16.741 --> 26:17.826
[Hyeong-seok sighs]

26:19.577 --> 26:21.705
He never spills anything.

26:21.788 --> 26:23.248
He just mopes on his own.

26:23.331 --> 26:26.251
Come on, you need
to talk about it to move on.

26:27.085 --> 26:30.463
Will talking about it
really help me move on?

26:31.047 --> 26:33.300
Then, I will.

26:33.383 --> 26:35.302
Go ahead. We're listening.

26:37.429 --> 26:39.723
[whispers] Sir, this won't take long.

26:45.353 --> 26:46.688
So I…

26:48.189 --> 26:49.274
I…

26:50.984 --> 26:52.319
Mmm… [inhales sharply]

26:54.404 --> 26:55.363
[Hyeong-seok sighs]

26:55.447 --> 26:57.240
He keeps things to himself.

26:57.324 --> 26:59.534
He's not the type to talk it out.

26:59.617 --> 27:02.162
He won't say a word
because it'll remind him.

27:03.747 --> 27:05.081
[sighs]

27:07.917 --> 27:08.918
I…

27:12.130 --> 27:13.965
went to see her.

27:16.009 --> 27:17.469
-At dawn.
-[man] At dawn?

27:18.470 --> 27:19.304
At dawn.

27:19.888 --> 27:21.639
That doesn't sound like a good time.

27:23.016 --> 27:23.850
And?

27:24.684 --> 27:25.810
Someone came out, and…

27:27.812 --> 27:29.814
[melancholy music playing]

27:33.234 --> 27:34.277
[sobbing] …she tells me…

27:35.487 --> 27:36.946
not to…

27:39.240 --> 27:41.159
I can't stop thinking about it. [groans]

27:42.118 --> 27:44.746
-It's killing me.
-Who came out?

27:44.829 --> 27:47.916
Hey, do you even have to ask?
[laughs dryly]

27:47.999 --> 27:50.835
He's going to have it rough for a while.

27:51.878 --> 27:54.756
Honestly, stop being a fool
and go buy some spring onions.

27:57.967 --> 27:59.135
No way…

28:00.804 --> 28:01.930
Another guy came out?

28:03.932 --> 28:06.267
Hey! And you just came back?

28:06.351 --> 28:08.395
God, I'm going to lose my mind.

28:08.478 --> 28:10.397
What's wrong with her? She's unbelievable.

28:10.480 --> 28:11.940
She seemed perfectly decent enough,

28:12.023 --> 28:13.900
-but she's a crazy…
-[inhales sharply]

28:14.692 --> 28:16.111
Shut your mouth.

28:16.194 --> 28:17.237
[Tae-seo scoffs]

28:17.320 --> 28:19.948
[slurring] You don't even know her.

28:20.031 --> 28:22.409
God, you idiot.

28:25.703 --> 28:27.997
-[Tae-seo] Give me a drink.
-[sighs wearily]

28:28.081 --> 28:30.417
All right. Drink up then.

28:39.717 --> 28:40.802
Get a hold of yourself.

28:40.885 --> 28:42.846
-[man] Are you done drinking?
-Yes, thank you.

28:42.929 --> 28:45.557
-Yeah, take good care of him.
-I will. [exclaims disapprovingly]

28:46.933 --> 28:48.727
I'll go get my car. Stay put.

29:10.039 --> 29:11.458
Eun-a.

29:12.667 --> 29:14.002
[shudders]

29:15.044 --> 29:16.296
[exhales heavily]

29:20.633 --> 29:21.760
[huffs]

29:23.428 --> 29:25.430
[emotional music playing]

29:31.978 --> 29:35.148
[Eun-a] <i>I was always so jealous</i>
<i>when Seoul would hold fireworks festivals.</i>

29:35.231 --> 29:36.232
It's right there.

29:38.193 --> 29:40.111
[chuckles softly] That way.

29:40.195 --> 29:41.571
It's that way.

29:41.654 --> 29:44.032
[Eun-a] Ah… So that's Yeouido.

29:49.662 --> 29:50.497
[sighs]

30:22.654 --> 30:24.072
[music fades]

30:25.156 --> 30:26.157
Mmm.

30:27.283 --> 30:31.120
It's fine now, but I'll have to come back
when it gets colder.

30:31.204 --> 30:34.165
When you've set a date,
get the original faucets and handles out.

30:34.249 --> 30:36.751
I'll come by when I have time
and restore everything.

30:36.835 --> 30:38.127
Thanks.

30:38.920 --> 30:40.129
[cellphone vibrates]

30:44.217 --> 30:46.219
[lighthearted music playing]

30:48.513 --> 30:50.014
[So-hyeon] The village chief's house.

30:50.098 --> 30:51.850
-[woman] Really?
-[So-hyeon] Yes. [chuckles]

30:51.933 --> 30:54.018
-No wonder why you seem familiar.
-Right?

30:54.102 --> 30:55.186
[chuckling] There she is.

30:55.270 --> 30:56.521
Goodness.

30:57.522 --> 30:58.773
Mom's here!

31:11.411 --> 31:12.620
[music fades]

31:12.704 --> 31:14.706
I told them I was your mom.

31:14.789 --> 31:17.166
That's why they handed
this place over so easily.

31:17.250 --> 31:21.045
I made a scene, saying I'd kill them all
if they messed with my daughter.

31:23.464 --> 31:25.675
You were in Korea this whole time?

31:25.758 --> 31:28.720
It costs a lot of money and time
to come here.

31:28.803 --> 31:30.763
Taking care of your situation came first.

31:30.847 --> 31:33.933
Then, I met some people. It was fun.

31:34.559 --> 31:37.312
Hey, a lot of those people
made it big thanks to me.

31:37.854 --> 31:38.688
[scoffs]

31:39.314 --> 31:42.025
They made it big on their own,
not because of you.

31:43.693 --> 31:45.945
You can sleep here if you want.

31:47.155 --> 31:50.158
[sighs] God, I'm starving.
Got anything to eat?

31:50.241 --> 31:52.452
I want to try some of your cooking.

31:53.578 --> 31:54.412
Let's go.

32:17.977 --> 32:19.354
Eun-a.

32:19.437 --> 32:21.105
I'm going to check out your room.

32:22.023 --> 32:23.441
Go ahead.

32:34.953 --> 32:35.954
[So-hyeon gasps softly]

32:37.538 --> 32:39.290
You made it all so quickly.

32:40.333 --> 32:41.918
I just steamed what I'd made before.

32:50.051 --> 32:52.679
[chuckling] It's delicious.

32:54.180 --> 32:55.556
You're a good cook.

32:57.767 --> 32:59.894
Why are you all curled up like that?
You're the owner.

33:00.645 --> 33:02.271
Don't start.

33:02.355 --> 33:04.440
[So-hyeon] You look pitiful.
I don't like it.

33:04.524 --> 33:07.986
Sit with your legs crossed.
You'll lose your luck eating like that.

33:08.736 --> 33:09.696
I'm not eating.

33:10.822 --> 33:13.908
That there…
I didn't have any soup, so it's corn tea.

33:20.623 --> 33:21.916
[So-hyeon] It's nice and toasty.

33:22.000 --> 33:23.918
Did you roast the corn yourself?

33:25.128 --> 33:26.379
Pack me a bunch when I go.

33:26.462 --> 33:27.672
So I can make it at home.

33:29.716 --> 33:30.758
It reminds me of Seon-gyu.

33:33.261 --> 33:35.805
[gentle music playing]

33:45.023 --> 33:46.524
Want me to steam some corn for you?

33:47.108 --> 33:48.818
Gosh, Eun-a.

33:48.901 --> 33:50.987
You should've given me those first.

34:01.873 --> 34:02.874
[music fades]

34:04.459 --> 34:08.838
I was actually here before I went
to Gangneung and met your dad.

34:10.006 --> 34:11.466
The village chief's house.

34:11.549 --> 34:13.426
I stayed there.

34:15.678 --> 34:18.973
I was gathering information in Tongyeong.
Then, I was supposed to go to Gangneung.

34:19.557 --> 34:21.350
But I just loved it here.

34:21.434 --> 34:24.062
There was plenty to work with too.
[inhales sharply]

34:24.687 --> 34:27.482
I really didn't want to go to Gangneung.

34:28.316 --> 34:29.484
But in that town,

34:30.485 --> 34:33.321
a man from Seoul
was living with his daughter

34:33.404 --> 34:37.033
as he made vegan dishes
with local vegetables he'd dig up.

34:37.658 --> 34:41.037
And that daughter
kept calling our local coordinator.

34:41.996 --> 34:44.874
"What time are you coming?
What should we prepare?"

34:45.500 --> 34:48.628
Apparently, she was really excited
about all of us coming.

34:48.711 --> 34:51.631
She was going to leave school early
in time for our arrival.

34:51.714 --> 34:53.132
Honestly,

34:53.216 --> 34:54.801
she was a funny one.

34:57.929 --> 34:59.388
Her name was Mo Eun-a,

34:59.972 --> 35:02.975
and she was eagerly waiting for us.

35:03.935 --> 35:05.269
That's why I went.

35:06.062 --> 35:07.480
And going there…

35:11.818 --> 35:13.402
was the best decision I ever made.

35:15.696 --> 35:17.698
[heartwarming music playing]

35:28.793 --> 35:30.419
I can't come back to Korea anymore.

35:32.630 --> 35:33.923
I'm getting married.

35:38.678 --> 35:40.680
Just kidding. [chuckles softly]

35:43.349 --> 35:44.517
What's wrong with you?

35:45.393 --> 35:47.353
My mom talks about you every day.

35:48.437 --> 35:50.898
I guess she loved it when you were around.

35:50.982 --> 35:54.235
She said when you left,
you told her you'd come back.

35:54.944 --> 35:56.195
Day and night, she'd…

35:56.279 --> 35:58.447
Don't use expressions like that.

35:58.531 --> 36:00.158
"Lose your luck." "Day and night."

36:00.241 --> 36:02.285
It's obvious you just
picked them up somewhere.

36:05.705 --> 36:07.206
My mom's dying.

36:09.542 --> 36:10.376
You fool.

36:10.459 --> 36:11.919
[Eun-a sighs in frustration]

36:12.503 --> 36:15.089
[So-hyeon] We're all dying as we grow old.

36:15.173 --> 36:18.009
-There's an obvious limit to life.
-[sighs]

36:33.149 --> 36:35.860
MO SEON-GYU

36:50.958 --> 36:51.959
[music fades]

37:02.094 --> 37:04.347
Did you pack the corn tea for me?

37:07.225 --> 37:09.685
Can you also pack me one of those baskets?

37:10.478 --> 37:12.021
My mom would love it.

37:13.773 --> 37:15.775
Two sets of chopsticks and spoons too.

37:15.858 --> 37:17.109
For me and my mom.

37:18.361 --> 37:20.029
I like the Korean ones.

37:20.947 --> 37:23.616
It's made of brass. Brass is better.

37:23.699 --> 37:25.326
I'll ship them to you.

37:25.409 --> 37:27.161
I was going to give them away anyway.

37:27.828 --> 37:28.704
What else?

37:31.290 --> 37:32.667
The nameplate.

37:35.002 --> 37:37.630
[slow instrumental music playing]

37:40.132 --> 37:41.467
No.

37:58.276 --> 37:59.902
[So-hyeon] Eun-a, are you asleep?

38:03.406 --> 38:04.407
[music fades]

38:27.013 --> 38:28.764
Do you want to…

38:31.142 --> 38:32.893
come to Hawaii with me?

38:34.854 --> 38:37.398
[pensive music playing]

39:35.331 --> 39:36.540
[music fades]

39:39.877 --> 39:41.587
[Eun-a] Eat the corn right away.

39:43.756 --> 39:46.801
[So-hyeon] I guess
the last thing I eat in Korea

39:46.884 --> 39:49.387
will be Mo Eun-a's steamed corn.

39:49.887 --> 39:51.013
How meaningful.

39:51.097 --> 39:53.265
I'm going to eat it at Incheon Airport.

39:56.102 --> 39:58.062
You should go. It's time.

39:59.313 --> 40:00.523
[So-hyeon] Mmm…

40:03.818 --> 40:04.902
Smile.

40:05.986 --> 40:07.780
I'm going to show it to my mom.

40:07.863 --> 40:10.533
Smile. Make it cute.

40:10.616 --> 40:13.661
-I'm 30.
-It's a beautiful age.

40:14.412 --> 40:16.580
-Give me a pretty smile.
-[camera clicks]

40:16.664 --> 40:17.873
[scoffs]

40:21.544 --> 40:22.878
[camera clicks]

40:24.380 --> 40:25.548
[camera clicks]

40:26.966 --> 40:28.342
[camera clicks]

40:30.136 --> 40:31.137
[chuckles softly]

40:35.433 --> 40:37.518
I've done everything I needed to do here.

40:38.853 --> 40:40.062
[exhales heavily]

40:54.618 --> 40:57.246
[gentle music playing]

41:02.668 --> 41:03.878
Take care.

41:06.630 --> 41:07.506
I'll miss you.

41:16.891 --> 41:17.975
[huffs]

41:27.985 --> 41:29.820
Can I go too?

41:38.579 --> 41:39.580
Can I also…

41:41.290 --> 41:43.709
go where you and your mom

41:45.044 --> 41:46.795
will be?

41:47.546 --> 41:48.672
Let's go right now.

41:49.465 --> 41:50.299
Pack your bags.

41:51.509 --> 41:53.093
You don't even have any guests.

41:54.136 --> 41:55.679
Can I really go?

41:55.763 --> 41:56.764
[chuckles]

41:56.847 --> 41:58.474
[voice breaking] Of course.

41:58.557 --> 41:59.975
Come with me.

42:03.687 --> 42:05.564
I need to wrap things up here first.

42:07.733 --> 42:10.236
[sniffles] I really…

42:11.779 --> 42:13.781
wasn't going to say this,

42:15.199 --> 42:16.992
but your room at my mom's house

42:17.076 --> 42:19.078
is exactly the way you left it.

42:20.162 --> 42:21.747
Don't you dare not come.

42:22.831 --> 42:25.376
What about your passport?
You need to check right away.

42:25.459 --> 42:28.420
If it's expired, get it reissued.

42:28.504 --> 42:29.338
When I go,

42:31.465 --> 42:33.717
I'll bring Dad's nameplate as well.

42:41.183 --> 42:42.643
[So-hyeon sniffles]

43:06.417 --> 43:08.419
[music fades]

43:09.878 --> 43:11.297
NOTICE OF CLOSURE AND FREE GIVEAWAY

43:11.380 --> 43:15.593
[Eun-a] <i>Thank you to all the guests</i>
<i>who have loved and supported Byeonnwi.</i>

43:16.302 --> 43:18.637
-[girl] Goodbye.
-[laughter]

43:18.721 --> 43:19.930
Bye.

43:20.014 --> 43:21.223
[man] We had a great stay.

43:21.307 --> 43:22.850
Thank you. Let's go.

43:22.933 --> 43:26.770
[Eun-a] <i>Byeonnwi will be accepting</i>
<i>reservations up until December.</i>

43:27.479 --> 43:28.522
[camera clicks]

43:28.606 --> 43:32.151
<i>We'll be giving away</i>
<i>our furniture and decorative items.</i>

43:32.234 --> 43:33.611
<i>If you are interested,</i>

43:33.694 --> 43:36.655
<i>please check the attached photos</i>
<i>and let us know.</i>

43:37.323 --> 43:38.365
<i>Thank you.</i>

43:38.449 --> 43:40.451
[pleasant music playing]

43:42.328 --> 43:44.246
[Ga-on's mom chuckling] Ga-on's excited.

43:44.330 --> 43:46.040
[chuckles]

43:49.668 --> 43:51.003
[music fades]

43:51.086 --> 43:52.379
Make good use of it, Ga-on.

43:54.214 --> 43:56.508
[Ga-on] That chair is my little brother.

43:56.592 --> 43:59.970
Really? The chair must be happy.
[chuckles]

44:00.054 --> 44:01.722
It's all been cleared out already?

44:02.848 --> 44:06.602
I allowed plenty of time on purpose,
but the giveaway happened really quickly.

44:08.604 --> 44:09.897
We're sad about it,

44:09.980 --> 44:14.026
so we all wanted to keep
at least something that came from here.

44:15.361 --> 44:17.613
What about your stuff?
I'm sure you have a lot.

44:17.696 --> 44:19.114
I've already shipped them.

44:19.198 --> 44:20.366
[sighs]

44:21.158 --> 44:22.451
So you're really leaving.

44:22.534 --> 44:24.536
You two were my last guests.

44:25.412 --> 44:26.830
Thank you for coming.

44:26.914 --> 44:28.540
Mom. A photo.

44:28.624 --> 44:30.292
-Should we take a photo?
-[Eun-a chuckles]

44:30.376 --> 44:31.960
-How about a photo?
-Shall we?

44:32.044 --> 44:33.379
Let's take it here.

44:34.338 --> 44:35.839
We'll take a selfie.

44:35.923 --> 44:37.216
Here we go.

44:39.051 --> 44:40.928
Cheese. One, two, three.

44:41.011 --> 44:42.054
[camera clicks]

44:42.137 --> 44:44.306
[heartwarming music playing]

45:32.563 --> 45:39.111
MO SEON-GYU

45:57.963 --> 45:59.089
[music fades]

45:59.173 --> 46:01.467
-Mr. Yeon Tae-seo.
-Yes?

46:01.550 --> 46:04.595
You already have experience
working as a subway operator.

46:04.678 --> 46:08.265
Is there any special reason why you want
to change jobs and be a rail operator?

46:09.349 --> 46:13.437
What did you find challenging
about your previous job?

46:14.271 --> 46:17.107
Ah… It's not that I found it challenging.

46:18.192 --> 46:21.195
I wasn't in a situation
where I could do that job, but…

46:22.905 --> 46:25.866
[slow instrumental music playing]

46:25.949 --> 46:28.368
[Tae-seo] <i>I wanted to become</i>
<i>a Sea Train driver back then.</i>

46:29.244 --> 46:31.663
<i>I guess it looked kind of cool.</i>

46:31.747 --> 46:32.789
[Eun-a] <i>That's nice.</i>

46:39.087 --> 46:42.424
It was the first job I chose
simply because I wanted to do it.

46:43.884 --> 46:45.344
It was very rewarding.

46:46.261 --> 46:49.389
It helped me feel like
I was finally self-reliant.

46:50.516 --> 46:54.061
I'd like to go beyond the city
and operate different types of trains

46:54.144 --> 46:55.562
across a wider range of terrain.

47:01.401 --> 47:02.402
[music fades]

47:02.486 --> 47:03.946
-Hello.
-[man] Hello.

47:04.029 --> 47:06.532
I heard you're changing jobs.

47:06.615 --> 47:07.699
No, not yet.

47:07.783 --> 47:09.493
I made it
to the final round of interviews,

47:10.244 --> 47:11.787
but I ended up rambling.

47:12.621 --> 47:14.164
I'm sure you'll get it.

47:14.706 --> 47:18.460
Oh. Since you're quitting,
this will be a good way to say goodbye.

47:19.920 --> 47:21.255
Here.

47:21.338 --> 47:23.048
-What is it?
-[man chuckles]

47:23.131 --> 47:25.842
I took it while I was taking
night photos at Oido Station.

47:27.135 --> 47:28.554
It came out pretty well.

47:28.637 --> 47:29.763
Thank you.

47:32.683 --> 47:33.934
All right then.

47:42.150 --> 47:43.735
[sentimental music playing]

47:45.362 --> 47:46.196
[Eun-a] <i>Tae-seo.</i>

47:47.239 --> 47:48.824
This is the right place.

47:49.449 --> 47:50.909
This place is what's real.

48:00.335 --> 48:01.461
[Tae-seo] <i>Eun-a.</i>

48:02.546 --> 48:04.298
<i>For you, that's the right place, isn't it?</i>

48:07.634 --> 48:08.677
[Chang-sik] Good job.

48:14.641 --> 48:16.018
[Tae-seo] <i>For me…</i>

48:26.695 --> 48:28.280
<i>this is the right place too.</i>

48:47.758 --> 48:51.261
Please let us both
achieve our goals today.

48:53.013 --> 48:53.972
[Tae-seo] <i>You're right,</i>

48:54.931 --> 48:56.350
<i>and I'm right too.</i>

48:57.225 --> 48:58.560
<i>But then,</i>

49:00.395 --> 49:02.439
<i>why did we end up like this?</i>

49:32.427 --> 49:33.720
[music fades]

50:01.957 --> 50:02.958
Can I help you?

50:04.167 --> 50:05.669
The guesthouse that was here…

50:06.545 --> 50:08.588
Ah. It's closed now.

50:10.215 --> 50:11.258
Then what about Eun-a…

50:12.342 --> 50:13.844
I mean, where is the owner?

50:14.428 --> 50:15.387
She went home.

50:15.470 --> 50:17.055
I heard she's going to her mom's.

50:18.223 --> 50:21.768
When my mom was pregnant with me,
she'd always crave these noodles.

50:21.852 --> 50:24.354
I'm sure she's doing well somewhere.

50:24.438 --> 50:27.733
Mmm. Somewhere that
has nothing to do with me.

50:27.816 --> 50:29.818
[gentle music playing]

50:30.527 --> 50:31.528
[sighs softly]

50:40.871 --> 50:42.956
[music fades]

50:47.544 --> 50:48.754
Huh.

50:48.837 --> 50:51.840
Maybe it's not a good idea
to go looking like this.

50:58.764 --> 50:59.598
[A-sol sighs]

51:00.348 --> 51:03.393
He said he was visiting Gangneung,

51:03.477 --> 51:05.020
so he should be back soon.

51:05.103 --> 51:06.646
[sighs deeply]

51:08.565 --> 51:10.567
Was getting a perm a bit over the top?

51:11.651 --> 51:13.653
[car approaching]

51:14.946 --> 51:17.491
Oh. I have to get out later though.

51:21.453 --> 51:22.370
Excuse me.

51:25.415 --> 51:26.333
Ah.

51:27.042 --> 51:28.335
What are you doing here?

51:29.920 --> 51:30.754
[A-sol] What?

51:31.421 --> 51:34.049
-[sighs]
-Don't tell me you forgot.

51:34.132 --> 51:36.718
Well, I just… Where should we go?

51:36.802 --> 51:39.221
-Did you pick a place?
-That hurts.

51:40.889 --> 51:43.391
Sorry, I'm a little… [inhales deeply]

51:44.267 --> 51:45.936
…out of it today.

51:48.063 --> 51:49.606
[sighs] Let's do this another day.

51:56.822 --> 51:58.365
Why put it off?

51:58.990 --> 52:00.408
Let's get it over with.

52:03.161 --> 52:04.120
What I said

52:04.204 --> 52:06.498
about my first breakup

52:07.290 --> 52:08.875
wasn't a joke.

52:09.626 --> 52:11.711
It's important to me.

52:12.546 --> 52:13.380
I know.

52:16.550 --> 52:19.553
[keypad beeping, dings]

52:25.308 --> 52:26.893
Let's turn on just the lamp.

52:26.977 --> 52:29.062
If it's too bright,
reality's going to hit hard.

52:37.863 --> 52:38.780
[switch clicks]

52:44.411 --> 52:46.037
[Tae-seo] I'll give you some water.

52:46.872 --> 52:47.706
Let's just do it.

52:47.789 --> 52:49.249
Come sit.

52:49.916 --> 52:51.084
[Tae-seo sighs softly]

52:52.669 --> 52:53.753
Sorry.

52:55.463 --> 52:56.715
Today, I…

53:03.305 --> 53:04.514
[Tae-seo sighs]

53:09.644 --> 53:10.478
[sighs]

53:13.899 --> 53:14.983
[A-sol] What about today?

53:15.901 --> 53:17.068
Today,

53:19.070 --> 53:20.864
I'm feeling really pathetic.

53:22.449 --> 53:24.159
We all have days like that.

53:25.368 --> 53:27.370
I felt like that earlier.

53:27.454 --> 53:29.331
Pathetic and embarrassed.

53:31.499 --> 53:33.001
Well, what did you do?

53:33.668 --> 53:35.462
What kind of pathetic
are we talking about?

53:38.381 --> 53:40.091
I was the one who broke it off,

53:41.301 --> 53:43.178
but I couldn't accept it.

53:43.762 --> 53:44.721
[sighs]

53:46.890 --> 53:47.933
I've heard enough. Mmm.

53:48.975 --> 53:50.060
Let's hurry and do this.

53:54.439 --> 53:55.607
[Tae-seo sighs]

54:02.739 --> 54:03.615
You're…

54:07.285 --> 54:10.956
breaking up with me because I'm pathetic.

54:11.748 --> 54:13.750
[gentle music playing]

54:16.044 --> 54:17.420
[A-sol sighs]

54:17.504 --> 54:20.757
Once we break up,
we won't see each other ever again.

54:21.591 --> 54:23.301
You'd know this better than me.

54:24.177 --> 54:25.637
We're holding hands,

54:28.181 --> 54:29.724
we're facing each other,

54:30.308 --> 54:32.268
and now, with warmth…

54:34.562 --> 54:35.563
[exhales heavily]

54:38.566 --> 54:39.859
Thank you.

54:40.819 --> 54:42.779
The study center's Seat One guy

54:43.488 --> 54:46.533
was the most unfortunate person I knew.

54:48.910 --> 54:52.998
<i>He was so pitiful</i>
<i>that I couldn't even dare to like him.</i>

54:53.748 --> 54:56.918
[sighs] <i>I was so sure back then</i>
<i>when I was young</i>

54:57.002 --> 54:59.170
<i>that your misfortune would last forever.</i>

55:00.922 --> 55:04.217
But you found your way and flourished.

55:04.968 --> 55:06.761
You also found love,

55:06.845 --> 55:08.763
went through a breakup,

55:09.806 --> 55:12.183
and you didn't let misfortune
weigh you down.

55:13.977 --> 55:16.187
You proved my preconceptions wrong

55:16.938 --> 55:18.898
and lived a good life, so I'm grateful.

55:20.775 --> 55:21.818
Also,

55:22.736 --> 55:25.071
thank you for showing me a miracle.

55:27.699 --> 55:31.453
The moment your grandma's finger twitched,
I witnessed a miracle.

55:33.538 --> 55:35.248
I won't ever forget it.

55:36.458 --> 55:40.628
Whenever things get tough,
I'll remember it.

55:41.296 --> 55:45.216
The finger twitch
of Seat One guy's grandma.

55:46.301 --> 55:47.635
I can't do this.

55:51.347 --> 55:52.724
[music fades]

55:52.807 --> 55:54.059
I can't do this today. Sorry.

56:25.173 --> 56:27.258
I can't handle seeing your back.

56:29.511 --> 56:33.223
At the study center,
all I saw was your back.

56:34.224 --> 56:37.977
On our way back
after your grandma woke up,

56:38.603 --> 56:41.231
I saw your back
when you got out of the car,

56:42.941 --> 56:44.692
and I managed to hold it all in even then.

56:48.738 --> 56:50.156
[emotional music playing]

56:54.244 --> 56:56.121
[Tae-seo sniffles]

57:15.223 --> 57:17.016
Let's go out for real.

57:20.937 --> 57:23.356
[sniffles] No, I mean…

57:23.857 --> 57:25.191
Oh… I mean…

57:27.444 --> 57:28.778
[A-sol clears throat, sniffles]

57:31.197 --> 57:33.074
Just until the end of the year.

57:34.784 --> 57:37.745
We can go out
and break up around Christmas.

57:38.872 --> 57:39.747
Hold on.

57:41.207 --> 57:44.377
Before Christmas would be better.
I'm busy at the end of the year.

57:44.461 --> 57:47.338
Maybe on the 23rd or the 24th.

57:48.756 --> 57:49.632
Or just do it today.

57:51.342 --> 57:52.927
You just had to say you couldn't do it…

57:54.179 --> 57:55.180
[Tae-seo sniffles]

58:06.357 --> 58:07.567
Never mind. Sorry.

58:07.650 --> 58:08.818
Let's do that.

58:14.032 --> 58:15.825
It won't even be that difficult.

58:24.083 --> 58:25.502
[music fades]

58:40.141 --> 58:42.143
[somber music playing]

58:57.116 --> 58:59.285
[Tae-seo] <i>That place where your mom is.</i>
<i>What's it like?</i>

59:06.251 --> 59:07.293
<i>Over there,</i>

59:08.378 --> 59:10.296
<i>the things I couldn't give you</i>

59:11.839 --> 59:14.300
<i>and the things you could never</i>
<i>be fulfilled by in this world</i>

59:15.718 --> 59:16.970
<i>can all be fulfilled, right?</i>

59:24.102 --> 59:25.895
<i>When I was crushed by misfortune,</i>

59:26.813 --> 59:31.150
<i>moving without purpose</i>
<i>and just simply breathing…</i>

59:34.404 --> 59:36.823
<i>you came to me so casually</i>

59:37.907 --> 59:42.954
<i>and gave me what the world</i>
<i>could never fulfill, Eun-a.</i>

59:50.837 --> 59:52.297
<i>I'll forever be…</i>

59:53.923 --> 59:55.091
<i>grateful.</i>

01:00:06.185 --> 01:00:08.187
[music fades]

01:00:10.648 --> 01:00:11.524
[Chang-sik sighs]

01:00:12.984 --> 01:00:14.110
I'm going to go.

01:00:15.028 --> 01:00:16.195
[Tae-seo] I'll take you home.

01:00:17.030 --> 01:00:19.324
No, it's fine. You'll be coming back here.

01:00:20.575 --> 01:00:22.493
It's just a quick trip
to go there and back.

01:00:25.038 --> 01:00:27.832
Uh… Did you take your medicine?

01:00:27.915 --> 01:00:29.167
Yeah.

01:00:29.250 --> 01:00:31.377
I'm just sore
because the tension wore off.

01:00:31.961 --> 01:00:33.046
I'm fine.

01:00:35.882 --> 01:00:37.175
[Chang-sik sighs]

01:00:37.258 --> 01:00:39.594
It looks like this will all be over soon.

01:00:49.354 --> 01:00:50.563
Grandpa.

01:00:51.147 --> 01:00:52.774
-So…
-Yeah?

01:00:52.857 --> 01:00:54.567
About me changing jobs…

01:00:55.860 --> 01:00:56.736
I didn't get it.

01:00:58.780 --> 01:01:01.783
You took a test and failed?

01:01:02.742 --> 01:01:03.576
[chuckling] Yes.

01:01:04.702 --> 01:01:06.204
I can take it again next year.

01:01:08.873 --> 01:01:10.083
I'm off to the hospital now.

01:01:10.667 --> 01:01:11.709
Okay.

01:01:18.758 --> 01:01:20.051
[exhales heavily]

01:01:52.458 --> 01:01:53.418
Mo Eun-a.

01:01:58.172 --> 01:02:01.092
[sentimental music playing]

01:02:21.320 --> 01:02:24.699
STILL SHINING

01:02:53.436 --> 01:02:55.438
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
